This is my first Counter-Strike: Source map. It is even the first map I have ever published for a PC game. The Story: A bunch of terrorists escaped in an old and trashy fishing boat from a prison. One of them played with some dynamite and put a hole in the boat. Thus it sank, but they were able to rescue themselves on a small island. To the misfortune of the terrorists a little speedboat of the counter-terrorists followed them and landed on the very same island. The counter-terrorist-unit is not allowed to make any prisoners. Highlights: The difference between fy_isle and standard fun yard maps is that it contains three different randomly selected gameplay modes: Headshot, Regular and Sudden Death. In the mode Headshot you have to shoot your enemy in the head to score. Or as an alternative you and some teammates have to shoot at him together to frag him. The mode Sudden Death is quite different to the one above. You can kill the opponent with a single shot. But be careful if you hurt youself you will be spectating the game. And finally, the mode Regular. This mode follows the usual CS:S-rules, except for the fact that you don't need to buy any weapons. Important notes: Do not under any circumstances go swimming. It's not good for you health. Additionally it is quite important to listen to the announcer since it is the only validate source for knowing which gameplay mode has been activated.

Hello and welcome to my best island level yet! It's very much like Battle Field 2, in that it has various areas on the map to take over and that it's nice and sunny. Choose your class at the beginning and take over the checkpoints. Get near the large metal pole in the enemy's base to win. Bots have great trouble on this map (In that it takes about 3 hours to generate the nav file and still doesn't seem to have an end). If somebody could generate the bot code I would be VERY greatful and you can have your name in the credits.

It needs the correct server cfg to work, hopefully a massive 32 man server could host this some day, though I doubt something this radical would work on a large scale. There is a drivable vehicle, though it's very basic.

Have fun climbing the massive mountain. It doesn't look big until you get to the top ;). A nice little bit of exercise for any explorers out there.

If you like this map then say, I'll make more maps like that then eventually I'll have enough to make a mod for css.

Thank you for reading, hopefully the map's fun ;)

It is actually V0_5c, but I doubt I'll add any more to it.

***FY_GARAGE(WITH SECRETS!) MAP MADE BY ROGUEGUY AND MEANING_IN_TRAGEDY***

This map is a fightyard map, but it has many many twists!

The Terrorists spawn in the main garage and the Counter-Terrorists spawn in the office.

There are MANY secrets in this map (About 20), that I have fully explained in the README.txt that comes with the map. I won't spoil them, but the secrets range from...

- Cars coming through walls
- Buttons that reveal hidden weapons
- Explosions
- Hidden ladders
- A jail (with a fun button on the outside :)
-Things falling out of ceilings (Just to scare you :)
-Floors that rot out when you step on them

That is just a preview of the secrets on this map :)

There are also 2 vent systems, one on the ground and one on the ceiling, that have holes in them for you to snipe out of.

Me and Meaning_In_Tragedy really worked hard on this map, and we hope you enjoy it!

A remake of fy_infiltrate, I found an old version of it and decided a good way to get back into mapping (Havent mapped in over a year) was to make a V2 cos there were quite a few issues with the old map. This is my first big map project, and it took almost ten times as long to make as the original, so dont be too harsh ^^

I've added so many details and fixes I cant really write it all down, you'll just have to play it and see. The most important additions are:

- 3D skybox and lighting fixes.
- Surrounding buildings and details.
- New underground area.
- A huge amount of bug and texture fixes
- A ton of extra decals and small details
- A few easter eggs, some easier to find than others ;)
- Loads of new props, layout fixes, glass, indoor textures....the list goes on...

Before you rate/assess it, please take the time to have a look at the original version (aswell as this version, ofc), which can be found here: 
http://www.fpsbanana.com/maps/45460

The map centers around a secret compound held by the CT's. T's start outside, CT's start in the warehouse. There are a huge number of possible attack routes for both teams to take.

See the DevNotes at the bottom left for all updates/fixes since release.
